Department store and supermarket sales inFebruary rose 3.7 pct from a year earlier to 1,080 billion yen,after a 2.6 pct year-on-year gain in January, boosted by highersales of clothes and food at department stores, the Ministry ofInternational Trade and Industry said.    The unadjusted total included department store sales of 559billion yen, up 5.1 pct from a year earlier, and supermarketsales of 521 billion, up 2.4 pct.    The seasonally adjusted store sales index (base 1985) fell1.5 pct to a preliminary 106.7 in February from 108.3 inJanuary compared with 102.9 a year earlier. REUTER&#3;